@node "overview" "MUILabeler - Overview"

         MUILabeler        (C) 1995  John M Haubrich Jr
                                     All Rights Under Copyright Reserved
         Version 1.3
         May 28, 1995


   MUILabeler prints mailing labels of user-defined size.  You can print
more than one label across and as many labels as you wish.  Each label
definition can be saved to a data file for later use.
@endnode
@node "requirements" "MUILabeler - Requirements"

   MUILabeler 1.3 requires the following:

      À  AmigaDOS 2.04 or higher.
      À  Magic User Interface 2.0 or higher.
@endnode
@node "startup" "MUILabeler - Starting MUILabeler"

   Start MUILabeler by double-clicking the tool icon or the icon of a
   data file.  You may also use the Shell:

      MUILabeler datafile
@endnode
@node "mainwdw" "MUILabeler - Window Layout"

   Enter the data for each label in the five string gadgets of the settings
   area.  Enter the lines for each label in the listview below.


   TYPE STYLES
                  ON             OFF
   À @{b}BOLD@{ub}         \\B             \\b
   À @{i}Italic@{ui}       \\I             \\i
   À @{u}Underline@{uu}    \\U             \\u
   À Plain        \\P or \\p

   Note that each line has its type style reset to Plain.

   For example, the lines:
      \\c\\BMUILabeler \\IVersion 1.3
      \\c(C) 1995
      \\c\\UBy John M Haubrich Jr.\\u

   will print like this:
      |    @{b}MUILabeler @{i}Version 1.3@{ui}@{ub}    |
      |           (C) 1995           |
      |    @{u}By John M Haubrich Jr.@{uu}    |


   @{b}Print@{ub} will print labels to the printer.

   The @{b}View@{ub} button will print a row of labels to the CONSOLE device.
   You may customize the output specification of the CONSOLE by using
   the @{b}Settings/Set Preview Console...@{ub} menuitem.


   Special buttons:
   À Clear  - Clear the list highlight.  In other words, make no item
              active.
   À Erase  - Erase the highlighted item.
   À Up     - Move the highlighted item up one line.
   À Down   - Move the highlighted item down one line.
@endnode
@node "settings" "MUILabeler - Settings Window"

   Enter the console spec for the View option.
   The CONSOLE (or CON:) string should follow the standard AmigaDOS
   format:

      CON:<leftedge>/<topedge>/<width>/<height>/<name>/<options>

      <options> can be:
         WINDOW0x<addr>  -- Use window pointed to by addr.
                            (May be on a custom, public or WB screen.)
         SCREEN <name>   -- Open on public screen <name>.

      The standard AUTO, CLOSE and WAIT options are appended to your
      CONSOLE spec.

      À  AUTO opens the window only after all data has been written.
      À  CLOSE attaches a close gadget to the window.
      À  WAIT keeps the window open until you close it.
@endnode
@node "mainmenus" "MUILabeler - Menus"

   Project |
   --------
      New                  - Clear all data from MUILabeler window.
      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      Open...              - Open a label data file.
      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      Save                 - Save a label data file.

      Save As...           - Save a label data file under the file name
                             you specify.
      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      Print                - Print the labels.

      Printer Setup...     - Runs the system Printer Preferences tool.
      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      About...             - Gives program author and version information.
      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      Quit                 - Quits MUILabeler.


   Edit |
   -----
      Cut                  - Cut currently highlighted line to clipboard.

      Copy                 - Copy currently highlighted line to clipboard.

      Paste                - Paste line from clipboard into list.

   Settings |
   ---------
      Device settings...   - Setup the CON: window spec for the View option
                             and the printer device (defaults to PRT:).
      ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      Load Settings        - Loads above settings from a file.

      Save Settings        - Saves above settings as default. (ENVARC:)

      Save Settings As...  - Loads above settings to a file.
@endnode
